      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Rowan: Okay. Well then, let me, let me just quickly run through my document to, I guess, just surface the high level thoughts and thinking.", "ts": 30.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Rowan: So what I did was I, again, I broke, I broke the system down into modules again", "ts": 80.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I did a little bit of research into the variety of tools that they suggested that we use. for the most part, it all like looks good to me.", "ts": 880.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "the tool that looked, the tool for doing like the, the first run seems to be like overwhelmingly a tool called Presidio", "ts": 1180.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "So that's everything I've, I've, I've done. reflecting on, so I haven't read the latest email that they sent last night", "ts": 1520.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "what I did for each of the modules as well, sorry, I've dropped the screen share", "ts": 1645.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I was about to ask that. So, yeah, I can, I can, I've kind of like done, I can go more deeply into some of these things", "ts": 2455.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Pop me the ticket again and then I'll dive into that.", "ts": 2650.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:01", "chapter:02", "chapter:03", "chapter:04", "chapter:05", "chapter:06", "chapter:07", "chapter:08", "chapter:09", "chapter:10", "chapter:11", "chapter:12", "chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="person:laura-gongas">
      <data key="d0">Person</data>
      <data key="d1">Laura Gongas</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d3">False</data>
      <data key="d4">0.95</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Laura: Oh, can I just interrupt one second? Yeah. I have one question.", "ts": 250.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Laura: Because we normally in the, so in the AI team, we actually, we don't call it that way, but we normally have the raw, the intermediate steps, and then the actual output.", "ts": 260.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Yeah. They, they've told us a lot about it. Microsoft is trying to sell it.", "ts": 1195.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Spacey, it's a, it's a very like traditional, approach for natural language tasks. ... it's normally good for an initial run, or for like quite simple cases.", "ts": 1420.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I like the way that you structured and divided by modules. I'll just go into details", "ts": 1620.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I think that we have to be a bit explicit. It does match, but I feel that Vanessa is not technical.", "ts": 1900.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "It is a risk of overfitting, but when, when it's such like a complex pipeline and you're doing a proof of concept, like normally you start in a domain", "ts": 2380.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "So I think that from here, I'll just review Rowan what you have. I think that we have selected that case. And then I'll send the email to them and we can start running like the extraction of the entities.", "ts": 2420.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:02", "chapter:03", "chapter:04", "chapter:07", "chapter:08", "chapter:09", "chapter:10", "chapter:11", "chapter:12", "chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="person:deon-kuhn">
      <data key="d0">Person</data>
      <data key="d1">Deon Kuhn</data>
      <data key="d2">True</data>
      <data key="d3">False</data>
      <data key="d4">0.95</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Deon: I looked into it... I'll forward it to Rowan as well. Or have you already, Dion? I've already done it, but now it's stuck in my art box.", "ts": 5.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Deon: Yeah. Cause I'm just thinking about something like address and location, whether or not that, that needs to be sort of pseudonymized as well", "ts": 700.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "cause I remember Momo and I saw it at an event and it was literally, the purpose was to consolidate all their disparate tools that they had for data processing and represented into one thing.", "ts": 950.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "something like an open source model, you might be able to self-host just for the one off or something like that could be an option.", "ts": 1460.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I think they're just trying to get, I think they're trying to get the high level thing right now, because I think they realize they keep getting it wrong with us.", "ts": 1580.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Not one, Laura, because they don't do OCR.", "ts": 1800.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Then, Rowan, what are you working on next?", "ts": 2450.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "I want you to independently do research on the system as it currently is. And what that ticket is asking, like without my input and just come up with ideas.", "ts": 2570.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:01", "chapter:04", "chapter:05", "chapter:07", "chapter:08", "chapter:09", "chapter:10", "chapter:11", "chapter:12", "chapter:13"]</data>
    </node>
