    <node id="decision:0001">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Use a two-layer raw/curated approach for the POC rather than full bronze/silver/gold, but add an intermediate layer for evaluation</data>
      <data key="d8">tentative</data>
      <data key="d9">["Full medallion bronze/silver/gold enterprise pipeline", "Raw and curated only (two layers)", "Raw, intermediate, output (three layers)"]</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Rowan: we may probably only need two layers, like a raw and a curated set rather than like a full on, like an enterprise pipeline", "ts": 230.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Laura: maybe just having the output won't give us like enough information to be able to evaluate all of them.", "ts": 290.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Rowan: Yeah. All right. Sounds good.", "ts": 300.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:02"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0002">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Reuse Azure Document Intelligence for OCR (already migrated from Tesseract); propose same as Kumulus for M1</data>
      <data key="d8">made</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Rowan: they had suggested that we use Azure document intelligence, which I understand now is like what we like, we've moved over from Tesseract onto that... So basically we've proposed the same thing.", "ts": 480.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:03"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0003">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Treat Rowan's entity model as aspirational/broad and let the sample-case chronologies and prior pseudonymisation definitions narrow it</data>
      <data key="d8">tentative</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Laura: for the graph representation, I think that what would be useful perhaps is to take the chronologies of the two sample cases and just check what is it that's listed there, because that means that that's the relevant information that we want.", "ts": 760.0, "source": "transcript"}, {"quote": "Rowan: So this could be almost like aspirational as we take it broader... so it can cover more cases. Okay. That's a good point.", "ts": 800.0, "source": "transcript"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:04"]</data>
    </node>
    <node id="decision:0004">
      <data key="d0">Decision</data>
      <data key="d1">Databricks over Microsoft Fabric for the data platform</data>
      <data key="d8">made</data>
      <data key="d10">Kumulus (endorsed by Rowan)</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
