      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "What Kumulus proposed against what we propose | Group | Kumulus proposed | We add / change | People: Patients and doctors named | Add 'other named individual'; add the legal-persona typing and the roles / rights / obligations layer | Organisations: Organisations, and who people work for | Keep; add DDS code and organisation type | Clinical detail: Not proposed (only a generic 'clinical event' bucket) | Add Drug, Dose, Procedure, Diagnosis, Allergy. Without these you cannot judge the cause of action | Identifiers: NHS numbers, IDs | Keep; pull them into one group so de-identification can target them in one place | Locations: Addresses, locations | Keep | Temporal / versioning: Versioned guidelines mentioned | Make time a first-class entity: a timeline event and a guideline version window | Roles / rights / obligations: Not proposed | Add the duty-of-care layer (carried from the patent); the deviation is the breach | Evidence traceability: Not proposed | Add: link every finding back to a document and page | The gaps worth raising with Kumulus: the clinical detail (the big one, without it there is no cause of action), the duty-of-care layer, time as a real entity, and evidence traceability. | Which entities are worth the effort | One way to think about where to spend effort: how hard each entity is to pull out of the documents, against how...", "ts": 703.3, "source": "vision"}]</data>
