    <node id="visual:0009">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">document</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "3. Tools (open-source and vendor). For most of these the official getting-started docs are more durable than any one video, so that is what is linked. | Neo4j: A database that stores information as a network of things and the relationships between them, rather than rows and columns, so 'who is linked to what' is the natural shape. Best link: Neo4j getting-started / intro (Neo4j official). | Microsoft Fabric: A Microsoft data platform that bundles storage, pipelines, diagrams and a network in a connected set... Best link: Microsoft Fabric docs (Microsoft official). | spaCy: A free Python library for building practical language-understanding pipelines (entity extraction, parsing and so on). It is fast to run and easy to extend, which is why it shows up in most production NLP stacks. Best link: spaCy course / usage (spaCy official). | AllenNLP: A research library for building advanced language-understanding models in PyTorch. Now in maintenance / less common now and the testimony... Best link: AllenNLP docs (AllenNLP). | GLiNER: A small, efficient model that finds named entities it has never seen before by being given the categories you want in plain language, without training it on thousands of hand-labelled examples. It is what makes a custom labeller workflow fast. Best link: GLiNER GitHub (maintainers). | MIMIC: Real-world anonymised de-identified hospital data sets... it is what gives the 'custom build' modules real-world data they can test or build to. Best link: MIMIC/PhysioNet docs (official model studio).", "ts": 923.0, "source": "vision"}]</data>
      <data key="d6">["chapter:05"]</data>
      <data key="d29">chapframe-05.png</data>
      <data key="d30">923.0</data>
      <data key="d31">document</data>
      <data key="d32">3. Tools (open-source and vendor). For most of these the official getting-started docs are more durable than any one video, so that is what is linked. | Neo4j: A database that stores information as a network of things and the relationships between them, rather than rows and columns, so 'who is linked to what' is the natural shape. Best link: Neo4j getting-started / intro (Neo4j official). | Microsoft Fabric: A Microsoft data platform that bundles storage, pipelines, diagrams and a network in a connected set... Best link: Microsoft Fabric docs (Microsoft official). | spaCy: A free Python library for building practical language-understanding pipelines (entity extraction, parsing and so on). It is fast to run and easy to extend, which is why it shows up in most production NLP stacks. Best link: spaCy course / usage (spaCy official). | AllenNLP: A research library for building advanced language-understanding models in PyTorch. Now in maintenance / less common now and the testimony... Best link: AllenNLP docs (AllenNLP). | GLiNER: A small, efficient model that finds named entities it has never seen before by being given the categories you want in plain language, without training it on thousands of hand-labelled examples. It is what makes a custom labeller workflow fast. Best link: GLiNER GitHub (maintainers). | MIMIC: Real-world anonymised de-identified hospital data sets... it is what gives the 'custom build' modules real-world data they can test or build to. Best link: MIMIC/PhysioNet docs (official model studio).</data>
      <data key="d33" />
      <data key="d34">d9c9d9d9d9d9d9c8</data>
    </node>
    <node id="visual:0010">
      <data key="d0">VisualContext</data>
      <data key="d1">diagram</data>
      <data key="d4">0.9</data>
      <data key="d5">[{"quote": "Kumulus Visualisation Draft #2 | Lucidchart | Share | Shapes | Risks and Mitigation Strategy | [Microsoft] CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) | We recommend a CQRS design pattern as required. | Processing Layer (Batch + Command Side): handles all heavy data crunching work and re-ETL/work... separate read and write... append-only fact store; immutable; foundational/sourcing... write-side updates (Power BI/PDF/JSON, Knowledge graph)... Guideline structuring; case-to-guideline comparison... Eventual / structured datasets | Serving Layer (Query Side = Query Side): optimised for application and user interaction... Cosmos DB ... Entity resolution workflows; Review tasks (human-in-the-loop); Read projections ... read-optimised projections (Spark/SQL)... | Flowchart toolbar | Microsoft La...", "ts": 1049.7, "source": "vision"}]</data>
